3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 183 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) Any air board that operates a commercial airport serving more than one million
6 (1,000,000) passengers annually may:
7 (a) Use small purchase procedures established by the Federal Aviation
8 Administration for expenditures that do not exceed the simplified
9 acquisition threshold identified in 2 C.F.R. sec. 200.88; and
