2 Section 3. KRS 183.525 is amended to read as follows:
3 (1) The ["]Kentucky aviation economic development fund["] is established in the State
4 Treasury. Beginning on July 1, 2000, all receipts collected under KRS Chapter 139
5 from the sales or use tax on aviation jet fuel shall be deposited in this fund.
6 (2) The fund may also receive state appropriations, gifts, grants, and federal funds and
7 shall include earnings from investments of moneys from the fund.
8 (3) Any fund balance at the close of the fiscal year shall not lapse but shall be carried
9 forward to the next fiscal year.
10 (4) The[ Transportation] cabinet shall use all moneys deposited in the fund or accruing
11 to the fund for the development, rehabilitation, and maintenance of publicly owned
12 or operated aviation facilities and for other aviation programs within the
13 Commonwealth that will benefit publicly owned or operated aviation facilities.
14 (5) The cabinet shall be prohibited from expending moneys deposited in the fund for
15 administrative costs incurred by the cabinet or for any purpose other than the
16 development, rehabilitation, and maintenance of publicly owned or operated
17 aviation facilities and other aviation programs benefiting publicly owned or
18 operated aviation facilities.
19 (6) The cabinet shall, no later than October 1 of each year, submit a report on the
20 use of funds in the Kentucky aviation economic development fund for the
21 previous fiscal year to the General Assembly through the Legislative Research
22 Commission.
